ğŸ“Š Key Insights

1ï¸âƒ£ Revenue Concentration
Revenue is heavily concentrated in a few key states such as Florida and California, indicating strong regional dominance.

2ï¸âƒ£ Pricing Strategy
Over 50% of vehicles were sold below market value (MMR).
This suggests a volume-driven strategy rather than a premium pricing approach.

3ï¸âƒ£ Regional Discount Behavior
Some states show significantly negative total price differences, indicating aggressive discounting, while others maintain more balanced pricing.
This reveals inconsistency in regional pricing governance.

4ï¸âƒ£ Revenue Volatility
Monthly revenue trends show strong fluctuations, suggesting demand seasonality and potential operational volatility.

ğŸ’¡ Business Interpretation

The dealership appears to prioritize sales volume over per-unit margin.
While this increases revenue throughput, a sustained discount-driven strategy may compress long-term profitability.
Regional pricing strategy could be optimized to balance competitiveness with margin protection.

